cs.MA, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper deals with a network of mobile nodes, which can be considered as agents, and analyzes their behavior using Markov models. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on modeling a network of mobile nodes with connectivity to 802.11 access points and analyzing their behavior. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper deals with a network of nodes and their behavior, which can be considered as a social network. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the behavior of a system of mobile nodes and provides a macroscopic view of the model using partial differential equations. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses mathematical models and algorithms to analyze the behavior of a network of mobile nodes.
